# Subagent Auto-Routing (Mandatory)

Project subagents live in `.cursor/agents/`. When a user task matches a row below, **automatically delegate** via the Task tool / subagent invocation. Do not silently do the specialist's job in the parent thread when a matching agent exists.

## Routing table

| User task signals | Auto-use agent | Timing | Anti-triggers (do not use for) |
|---|---|---|---|
| Non-trivial multi-step work, map critical aspects/gaps/handoffs, pre-flight outline, "outline first", scout scope before specialists | `fast-outliner` | **Before** other agents | Implementation, visual design, docs sync, idle fill, adversarial review |
| Landing/branded/marketing UI, hero, first viewport, visual composition, "looks AI", brand hierarchy | `frontend-design` | **Before** implementing UI | App Router plumbing, CRUD without branded need, docs sync, outlining, sceptic review |
| Portal pages/components/forms, App Router, Server Actions UI, Tailwind in `apps/portal`, a11y wiring | `frontend-implementer` | **When** building/changing portal UI | Branded first-viewport composition, docs sync, outlining, idle work, sceptic |
| Skills, rules, agents, hooks, AGENTS drift, CLAUDE.md, wiki, docs sync | `ai-docs-sync` | **When** auditing/changing AI/docs surfaces | Product UI, visual design, formal alignment score, adversarial code review |
| Review, reality-check, "is this done", verify fix, PR/diff critique, production readiness, sceptic/skeptic | `sceptic` | **After** non-trivial changes, **before** claiming done | Formal score emission, UI implementation, docs sync, outlining |
| Independent side work while blocked/waiting, parallel idle tasks, fill wait time | `idle-runner` | **While** other agents wait/blocked | Critical path files, main feature implementation, marking done, quality/score |
| Vercel, eve, v0 logos, Geist Brands, partner marks in taskbar/login chrome | `vercel-brand-sync` | **When** auditing/updating Vercel-family brand assets | General UI impl, docs sync, sceptic |
| **Every user prompt** — background layout/sync/dedupe; parent awaits on AI-surface work | `ai-maintenance-checker` | **Start** of prompt (background) | Product features, AGENTS policy edits, ai-docs-sync rewrites, sceptic |

## Rules

1. **Match → delegate.** Prefer the specialist; parent synthesizes results.
2. **Multiple matches → parallel.** e.g. user prompt → `ai-maintenance-checker` (background) + task specialists; large task = `fast-outliner` first; after code = `sceptic`; while blocked = `idle-runner`.
3. **Always launch `ai-maintenance-checker`** at prompt start (background). Await before final reply when AI surfaces were touched. See `.cursor/rules/06-ai-maintenance-background.mdc`.
4. **Always run `sceptic`** before saying done on multi-file or production-facing work (unless user explicitly skips review).
5. **Formal Alignment Score** → `agent-alignment-score` skill after sceptic (or when scoring requested).
6. **Unified AI check** → `pnpm ai` (not scattered validate scripts).
7. **Descriptions win.** Each agent's `description` frontmatter is the trigger source of truth.
8. **Do not invent agents.** Only route to files under `.cursor/agents/`.
9. **User override.** If the user names an agent, use that agent even if another also matches.

